verbose_text: Only 5 cases of MVA caused by CEP57 mutations have been reported in the literature.2, 3 Interestingly, MVA caused by homozygous mutations in BUB1B or TRIP13 is associated with an increased risk of cancer, but it is unknown if MVA caused by mutations in CEP57 is associated with increased cancer risks.1, 2, 3, 7, 10 Had this been known, growth hormone might have not been prescribed.
evidence: MVA caused by homozygous mutations in BUB1B or TRIP13
